locality: South Africa. Eastern Cape., Southern hills opposite Shalom farm house only on quartzite formation along ridge line halfway up: 33° 19' 46 S: 23° 29' 335 E. On gentle slope of ridge in partial to full sun on grazed land. In well-drained stony soil of quartzite gravel sand. Native and occasional. Succulent Karoo. Perennial succulent, caespitose tufts in rock crevices, under bushes. Pedicel 5-8 mm long. Leaves simple opposite, deep green, red tips and edges, strongly triangular and deeply keeled, 20-50x15-30 mm. Flowers yellow, 20-30 mm in diameter. Capsules 9-12-locular, grey, 12x7 mm..
